PostMan – API testing tool
We can do manual testing of API’s using postman.

We have Desktop version also Web version – Desktop version just to install the application and open. Web version always need to open in the browser.

Postman download link: https://www.postman.com/downloads/
What is Workspace?
Workspace is an area where we maintain files and saved.

Create a new workspace
1>Top menu bar clicks on workspace
2>Click on create workspace
3>Blank workspace
4>Name -> My Workspace
5>Workspace type –> Internal
6>Manage access->Only you & invited people
7>Click on create

To Rename workspace Name
1>Top menu bar Select the workspace
2>View all workspace
3>Select the workspace which you want to rename
4>Just click on workspace name
5>Change the name and click on enter

To Delete the workspace

1>Top menu bar clicks on workspace
2>View all workspace
3>Select the workspace which you want to delete
4>click on settings
5>scroll down and click on delete workspace
6>Now type delete and click on delete workspace

What is collection?
Collection – Contains number of folders and http request.
Collection has multiple operations – create, rename, delete, run the collection (execute all the scripts)

We can create any number of collections under workspace.

Create a new collection
1>Click on file from top menu bar
2>Click on new
3>Select collection
4>Give the name and click on enter

If you want to share your collection, move, rename, duplicate, delete and export just select the collection and click on 3 dots.

Request----->API----->Response

Http requests
Get-> retrieve the resource from database
Post-> create resource on database
Put->update existing resource on database
Patch-> update the partial details of resource on database
Delete-> Delete existing resource from database

