Http Status Codes

1>Level 200  Success
•	200: OK  Success! Everything worked exactly as expected.
•	201: Created Your request created a new resource.
•	202: Accepted We will get to your request once it is your turn in line.
•	203: Non-Authoritative information.
•	204: No content Success, but nothing to show. Like a successful deleted.

2>Level 300  Redirection
•	301: Moved PermanentlyThis moved permanently. Update your bookmarks!
•	302: FoundTemporarily elsewhere. Like crashing at a friend’s place.
•	304: Not modifiedNo change, your cached version is still fresh.
•	307: Temporary Redirect Same as 302 but promises to keep the same HTTP method.

3>Level 400  Client Errors
•	400: Bad Request Sorry, your request doesn’t make sense.
•	401: Unauthorizedwho are you? You need to log in first before you can access.
•	403: Forbidden we know you, but you cannot touch this. Access denied!
•	404: Not FoundThe classis! This page has vanished into the digital void.
•	409: Conflict

4>Level 500  Server Errors
•	500: Internal Server Error Something went wrong on our servers. Wake the devs!
•	501: Not Implemented
•	502: Bad Gateway The server got a weird response from another server.
•	503: Service Unavailablewe’re temporarily closed for maintenance.
•	504: Gateway Timeout One server gave up waiting for another server. Too slow!
•	599: Network Timeout
